#chapter(15, "Kazugai Uta's faint voice in the dusk")[
  _"Haizz... What a tiring day..."_

  Kazugai Uta's home resided in a pretty remote suburb area outside of Tokyo,
  which took her about a 30 minute trip to get home from school. Hence, ever
  since middle school, she had gotten used to having to leave the train much
  later from her friends.

  Today had been quite a long day for her. She was approached by all sorts of
  people because of her friend Mona, to the point she was still talking to some of
  them at this exact moment. While there were some guys who just wanted to ask things
  about Narumi Sena and her younger sister,
  she had a couple of interactions that soon
  diverged from the original topic, which gave her some brand new friends.

  The scenery outside the train was no longer that of a populous city, but
  rather a more peaceful suburb urban area. For Uta, this was about halfway to
  her home.

  // apiss mentioned RAHHHHHHHH
  "Rika: So yeah, I was talking about that Alice show."\
  "Rika: Y'know, I'm so hyped up for that!"

  "Uta: The original story is pretty good, yeah."\
  "Uta: I wonder how good the adaptation would go."\
  "Uta: It'd be funny if it turned out to be the new _Powerpoint Hit_..."

  Uta giggled. Even though school ended, her daily chore of messaging to her
  classmates has not. Though it could feel like a chore sometimes, the
  giggle she just let out implied that she was kind of enjoying it.

  "Rika: Please don't! That was like a generational fumble..."\
  "Rika: I still can't believe my eyes that the animation was THAT bad."\
  "Rika: What on earth was the production committee thinking..."\
  "Rika: Ah! y'know about _Tea Party at the End of the World_?"

  "Uta: Hmm?"\
  "Uta: It just got a staff announcement, right?"

  _Tea Party at the End of the World_, or _Tea Party_ for short, was a magical
  girl manga that recently got an anime adaptation announcement. Being one of
  the most popular shoujo manga on Magica☆Stella, the anime was widely
  considered as one of the most anticipated upcoming release.

  Though, Uta did not really care about the franchise in particular.
  She tended to prefer more obscure anime than the stuff people tended to
  discuss a lot of. On the Internet, they called anime fans like her contrarians
  or something, but it was just that obscure anime had some "aura" that made
  them more lovely than the popular releases, at least for Uta. Nevertheless,
  despite not caring much about popular anime such as _Tea Party_, Uta was still
  very well-informed about such releases.

  "Rika: Uhm, I skimmed through the list, and it was more disappointing than I
  think."

  "Uta: Uh huh."\
  "Uta: At least it's still a reputable studio, right?"

  "Rika: HanaWorks-san are generally good with these kinds of shows, but I'm
  suspecting they would offload much of the work to offshore companies, though."

  "Uta: That's true, there is definitely the trend of outsourcing these days..."

  "Rika: Oh, right... I thought there was nothing, but is this Narumi Sena-san's
  dad?"

  Then, a screenshot of the _Tea Party at the End of the World_ staff
  announcement post was sent to Uta. There was a big red circle, hastily drawn by
  the one she was messaging with, on the name Narumi Yusuke.

  "Uta: It was the same kanji characters... No way, could this be real?"

  "Rika: See what I mean! There is no way that this could be a coincidence,
  right?"

  Uta felt a sense of déjà vu. She went back to the original post to check, and
  the name was definitely there. There's an obscure rumor that Narumi Sena's dad
  was a relatively unknown music composer, but his name was not explicitly
  revealed anywhere. Was this be a mere coincidence, or something more sinister?

  "Uta: I'm intrigued."

  "Rika: Same here. Imagine if it turns out to actually be her dad after all."

  Uta pondered a bit. _"There could be no way that this is true, right?"_
  Then, she realized that she had thought the exact same way when Mikoto
  asked her about the mysterious classmate named Narumi Mona. _"Wait, Mona?"_

  Uta realized that she had someone to confirm this fact.

  "Uta: Ah! I'm gonna ask Mona about it."

  "Rika: Nice idea! He's Narumi-san's dad too. Once you're done, share the
  results to me please!"

  "Uta: Okay! I'm gonna message her right now."

  _"If this suspicion is true, then her family is really stacked..."_

  Uta navigated to her messaging thread with Mona. Compared to the thread she's
  just talked on, this one was much, much shorter. It was just the message she
  sent her out of concern for the situation this morning. Aside from that, Uta
  did not have much to talk about with Mona, and to be fair, they mostly
  interacted at school, rather than through a messaging app.

  At least now there would be a topic for her to strike a new conversation. She
  forwarded the announcement picture before sending a message,

  "Uta: Mona! Is this really your dad?"

  Learning from Mikoto's advice, which Uta still seemed to doubt, she did not
  send along any emotes or stickers with her message.

  Briefly after, the status of her message changed from 'Sent' to have been
  'Seen'.

  _"She saw it..."_

  Knowing Mona, Uta knew that it would be a while until she would get a proper
  answer. Well, she did not have any problem with it, as it is not some urgent
  matter or anything like that. More than anyone, Uta knew that people reacted
  differently to smartphone messages. Some could reply instantly, but those who
  were more inexperienced would need more time for some whatever reason. Well,
  messages were not a school assignment or something, so she just gave people
  time to breathe.

  Right then, a message was announced on the train.

