  "We are arriving at Naka-meguro Station. Thank you for using Inochi Railway
  today..."

  It was the ever-familiar train annoucement voice, with a bit of static noise
  blended in.

  // "putting the fries in the bag"
  With this, Uta's brief train ride had finally gotten to an end.
  Putting the phone into her bag, she was ready to get out of the train to go
  back home. She sent a quick good-bye to the girl she was messaging with
  earlier, before hopping off the train.

  Stepping out of the door, she was met with the fresh air and the sunset of her
  home city. It was a scene that could awaken a special feeling in anyone, but
  for Uta, it was just yet another day.

  Meguro City, the place where Uta lived at, was a suburb region pretty close to
  Tokyo.

  Compared to the populous and bustling Tokyo, Meguro was a much quieter and
  comforting place. Though, it was still a city, so it was much more crowded
  with people than the countryside regions.

  A major downside of living this far to Tokyo was that Uta had to board two
  30-minute train rides every day to school, which was not the end of the world
  but rather a hassle. It was the same situation for her family members too, but
  recently, her parents had their work relocated close to where they lived.
  They wanted to get a house in the middle of Tokyo for their children,
  but it was nothing other than a fever dream, considering the never-ending rise
  of house prices.

  Uta began to walk on the same road back home from the station. The crowd
  surrounding her soon dissipated, which seemed to trigger a switch in Uta's
  mind.

  "Talking bad about your friend like that is not cool, my streamer."

  She slipped out a voice from her head. The accidental "badmouthing" of Mona
  still lingered on her mind, it seemed.

  "I'm sorry, okay. It's an honest mistake, please forget it."

  "What would poor Mona-chan think about that? Hmm, 'Uta-san must be a very nice
  person, why would she randomly badmouth me like that? Maybe she is not
  actually as nice as it seems...'"

  "Right! She would start to doubt you lying ass, which is a totally right thing
  to do! Honestly, I'm glad for her to realize the true wickedness of this bitch."

  "Please, can we talk about something else? Like the Narumi Yusuke thing, perhaps?"

  "After that whole Narumi Mona incident, I'd not be surprised if it's actually
  him. Also, that's a very poor attempt of changing the subject, streamer-san."

  "But Rika-chan really has an eye for detail. Meanwhile our streamer, I still
  remember her insane throw in that History question."

  "Stop! do not mention it here, I beg of you."

  "'Who is the Prime Minister of Japan in the 1970s?' Imagine living in
  Meguro and not getting such a simple question right."

  "I told you, I mistook it with the interim guy from post-WW2! Ahhh-, if I got
  that one right, my grade would be much better... I lost all mark for that
  problem because of that mistake."

  "This is why you never stay up late to study for exams, kids..."

  "Shut your ass up, won't you?"

  Kazugai Uta had a deep secret.

  She liked to role-play as an IRL streamer AND her chat at the same time.

  It’s like the eight-grader syndrome in light novels, but it seemed to begin
  much before she entered eighth grade. Sometimes, she could not control this
  side of her, and ended up mumbled something to her friends. Fortunately, the
  most notable response she got was a “You said something?”, so it seemed like
  no one had actually found out about this little secret of her. But if it were
  to be let out somehow, it would be embarrassing to death.

  It all began some time back when she was in middle school. She already had a
  habit of talking to herself, but back then, livestreaming was blowing up, and
  she randomly decided to act like one. She even came up with her own original
  lore, as an alien on a mission to Earth to collect "human emotion samples",
  whatever that might mean. The livestream was just her documenting her
  experience to her home planet.

  She suddenly sensed a vibration from her phone in the bag, which she quickly
  reached in to check if something happened. It was Mona, who answered her
  question from earlier.

  "Let's see... 'Uhm- that's right.' Chat, it's actually real..."

  "No way it's actually canon. So Mona's family truly is _that_ huge. Unlike a
  particular streamer..."

  "Was there some rumors about her mom being Narumi Ayako too? That extremely
  popular fashion designer? Meanwhile, our Uta is..."

  Despite Uta originating from an extraterrestrial civilization, she still
  considered her Earth family as her real family. Well, her original lore had a
  bunch of plot holes like these.

  "Hey, are you talking bad about my FAMILY? So vulgar..."

  "Yes.", a voice immediately replied.

  "Based.", and another followed.

  "You all are so..." Uta sighed, "You all talk about Mona like you are some
  saints, but then you immediately say obscene stuff like this. Really no shame,
  aren't you?"

  "Better than some streamer who could only talk about Alice brainrot."

  // LMFAO the throw of MLDM
  "And someone who made some _legendary_ fumbles during the entrance exams."

  "Did someone mention Alice? Alice is peak. Alice is my reason to live. Alice is
  cinema. Absolute peak, masterful writing. And of course the chat could not
  comprehend any of it, this chat is so ass man..."

  "There she goes."

  "More Alice brainrot incoming."

  Alice was an abbreviation for the _-273.15#[#math.degree]C_ anime, named after
  the titular character.
  For some, it was a masterpiece in recreating a post-apocalyptic atmosphere
  with its theme of nuclear winter and stuff. Uta tended to yap nonstop about
  the show to the imaginary chat, even after already rambled enough to a bunch
  to real people, such as her new friend Rika from earlier.

  "Chat, you have no sense of art at all. You need to know, that Alice, really
  was the pinnacle of story writing. So many layers of interpretation, which not
  only applies to working people such as the author, but also a mere student
  like me. Ah right, it might apply to your bunch of jobless nitwits, too! But
  you would never get it, I'm afraid..."

  "Hey, censor that word! Chat, our streamer use the j-word again! Please,
  // wait is that the SUICIDAL number????
  moderators, ban her for the next 14 days, please!"

  "See, all you talk about was stolen jokes from PikPok! So unoriginal..."

  Uta and "her chat" would continue to happily bicker with each other on her
  road home. She said everything out loud, including the chat's supposed
  messages as well as her lines. If an outside observer was watching this, it
  would be something akin to a monodrama, which would make them pretty weirded
  out, yeah.

  "Uta-nyan, do you have something on your mind?"

  "Not really... I am just tired."

  Her tone suddenly shifted. It was a playful one, something taken straight out
  of a chill gaming stream to something heavier, like when a streamer was about
  to express her feelings. Honest. Gentle. It was a voice she shared to no one,
  even her closest friends at school.

  "Well, being noble to others truly is hard, right?"

  "It's been only two days, and Uta-nyan feels like she does not have any energy
  remaining..."

  Uta sighed.

  "Chat, I don't want to admit, but maybe I'm not cut out for this..."

  "Of course, right! Uta is not a good person, so just doing something good for
  the sake of others wear her out."

  "Hey, don't take advantage of the situation to roast me, you dumb fucks."

  Ignoring Uta's interjection, the chat pressed on.

  "Repenting for ones' sins is hard! Especially if you're a horrible person like
  Uta-nyan..."

  "I told you to stop... Haizz"

  Even so, the two sides seemed to agree. Normally, Uta would fight with her
  chat over the most trivial things. But right now, the two seemed to finally
  agree on something for once.

  "Anyway, you need to lock in right now! If you want to pay all that debt, you
  must act now!"

  "Act now? No way! I'm tired as hell here!"

  "Stop bitching, Uta-nyan."

  "More like y'all STOP DOOMPOSTING AND JUST LET ME FOCUS ON THE WORK.
  Can we have LESS BRAINROT in this chat and actually have meaningful
  discussions?" Uta groaned in frustration towards her annoying chat.

  And the discussion returned to its upbeat state.

  "Not with that attitude, it seems."

  "I think Uta-nyan is unsavable, just my two cents (two cents is my entire
  life-saving)."

  And there she went, continuing her banter with herself. Such conversations
  were something that belonged to her, and only her, for now.
